ther test files to remove auto-commit assertions\n5. Run `mise run test:integration` to verify all tests pass\n\n### Phase 5: Update Documentation\n1. Update `CLAUDE.md` (remove auto-commit sections, simplify strategy documentation)\n2. Update `README.md` (remove auto-commit examples and references)\n3. Update `GEMINI.md` (mirror CLAUDE.md changes)\n4. Update architecture docs in `docs/architecture/`\n5. Update skills/agents documentation\n\n### Phase 6: Cleanup and Polish\n1. Review shared strategy code for any auto-commit remnants\n2. Search for remaining \"auto-commit\" or \"auto_commit\" strings\n3. Consider if strategy selection UI is still needed (setup.go)\n4. Consider if debug command needs simplification\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n```bash\nmise run test\n```\nShould pass after removing auto-commit tests.\n\n### Integration Tests (CRITICAL)\n```bash\nmise run test:integration\n```\nMust pass after converting resume_test.go and worktree_test.go to manual-commit.\n\n### Full CI Suite\n```bash\nmise run test:ci\n```\nRuns both unit and integration tests - must pass before merging.\n\n### Linting\n```bash\nmise run fmt && mise run lint\n```\nEnsure code formatting and lint checks pass.\n\n### Manual Verification\n1. Run `entire enable` - should work without strategy selection\n2. Run `entire status` - should show manual-commit as strategy\n3. Run `entire debug` - should not show auto-commit subcommand\n4. Verify session workflow: UserPromptSubmit → Stop → PostCommit hooks work correctly\n\n## Key Decisions\n\n### How to Handle Existing Auto-Commit Users?\n**Decision: Automatic migration with one-time warning**\n\nAlternatives considered:\n1. ❌ **Fail with error** - Would break existing users' workflows\n2. ❌ **Silent fallback** - Would confuse users who wonder why their setting isn't being respected\n3. ❌ **Manual migration command** - Adds friction and requires user action\n4. ✅ **Automatic migration with warning** - Best user experience, transparent, and one-time\n\nImplementation approach:\n- Migration happens in `settings.Load()` function\n- Detect `strategy == \"auto-commit\"` after loading and merging settings\n- Print clear warning message to stderr explaining the change\n- Update settings file(s) to use \"manual-commit\"\n- Gracefully handle read-only files (log warning but don't fail)\n- Migration happens once - subsequent runs won't trigger warning\n\n### Keep or Remove Strategy Selection?\nSince there's only one strategy now:\n- **Option 1**: Remove strategy selection entirely from `enable` command - simplify to just enable manual-commit\n- **Option 2**: Keep strategy infrastructure for potential future strategies\n- **Recommendation**: Keep infrastructure (registry.go, Strategy interface) but simplify setup.go to not prompt for strategy selection\n\n### Simplify Debug Command?\n- Current: `entire debug auto-commit` subcommand\n- After removal: Only manual-commit remains\n- **Recommendation**: Keep `entire debug` command but remove strategy-specific subcommands\n\n### Documentation Simplification\n- Current: Heavy emphasis on comparing two strategies\n- After removal: Focus on how manual-commit works\n- **Recommendation**: Rename \"Session Strategies\" to \"Session Management\", remove comparison tables\n\n## Verification Checklist\n\nAfter implementation:\n- [ ] All files deleted (3 files)\n- [ ] Settings migration implemented and tested\n- [ ] Migration warning message displays correctly\n- [ ] All tests pass (`mise run test:ci`)\n- [ ] Linting passes (`mise run lint`)\n- [ ] No remaining \"auto-commit\" or \"AutoCommit\" references in code (except historical CHANGELOG)\n- [ ] Documentation updated (CLAUDE.md, README.md, GEMINI.md, architecture docs)\n- [ ] `entire enable` works without strategy selection\n- [ ] `entire status` shows manual-commit\n- [ ] `entire debug` works (no auto-commit subcommand)\n- [ ] Resume functionality tested with manual-commit\n- [ ] Worktree functionality tested wit